                             </p>
                                                      <p>
                                              Michael J. Bennett, "Cosmic Diagrams: Incised Geometric Personal Ornaments at Harvard", <em>Teaching with Objects: The Curatorial Legacy of David Gordon Mitten</em>, ed. Amy Brauer, Harvard Art Museums (Cambridge, MA, 2010), pp. 148-59, fig. 4-5
                             </p>
                                    </dd>
        
                  <dt>Exhibition History</dt>
          <dd>
                          <p>
                              <em>From Pasture to Polis: Art in the Age of Homer</em>, Museum of Art and Archaeology, University of Missouri, Columbia, 10/09/1993 - 12/05/1993
                            </p>
                      </dd>
        
                  <dt>Subjects and Contexts</dt>
          <dd>
                          <p>Ancient Bronzes</p>
                      </dd>
        

        
      
      
        
                          <dt> </dt>
          <dd>
                        <p>This record has been reviewed by the curatorial staff but may be incomplete. Our records are frequently revised and enhanced. For more information please contact the Division of Asian and Mediterranean Art at <a href="mailto:am_asianmediterranean@harvard.edu"><span>am_asianmediterranean@harvard.edu</span></a></p>
                        </dd>
                      </dl>
    </div>
